wtd.co.uk (Those Were The Days) | accessdate = 25 March 2020 | date = 3 May 2005 | title = Davis Wins Players' Award }}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nClarke has played at various levels for the [[Republic of Ireland]]. He has made 45 appearances at under-16, under-17, under-18, under-19 and under-21 scoring 14 goals. In May 2008 he played in the inaugural Intercontinental Cup in [[Malaysia]].<ref name=\"sm110508\">{{cite news|url=http://www.sportsmalaysia.net/2008/05/11/intercontinental-cup-2008-republic-of-ireland/|title=Stokes heads a young \u00c9ire squad|date=11 May 2008|publisher=sportsmalaysia.net|accessdate=14 July 2009}}{{dead link|date=October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*[http://www.soccerscene.ie/ss_gen/player.php?id=199&level=ss17 Republic of Ireland U17 profile] at Soccer Scene\n*[http://www.soccerscene.ie/ss_gen/player.php?id=299&level=ss19 Republic of Ireland U19 profile] at Soccer Scene\n*[http://www.soccerscene.ie/ss_gen/player.php?id=17&level=ss201 Republic of Ireland U21 profile] at Soccer Scene\n\n{{Grimsby Town F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Clarke, Billy}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association footballers from Cork (city)]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland association footballers]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland expatriate association footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Scotland]]\n[[Category:Ipswich Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Colchester United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Falkirk F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Northampton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Darlington F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Brentford F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Blackpool F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Sheffield United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Crawley Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. player